The American Heritage dictionary defines '''ticky tacky''' as "[[Shoddy]] material, as for the construction of [[standardized housing]]". [http://www.bartleby.com/61/57/T0205700.html] Merriam-Webster dictionary defines it as "leazy or shoddy material used especially in the construction of look-alike tract houses". [http://www.m-w.com/dictionary/ticky%20tacky] It is famously used in this context by [[Malvina Reynolds]] in the song ''[[Little Boxes]]'' - which is used as the opening song to the Showtime series ''[[Weeds]]''.

'''Ticky tacky''' may also refer to [[tar paper]].

